        asdf
      </p>
    </solution>
  </task>
  
  <task>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Prove that the pullback <m> \preceq_{ f } </m> of a partial order <m> \preceq </m> on a set <m> Y </m> along a map <m> f \colon X \to Y </m> is a partial order on <m> X </m> if and only if <m> f </m> is injective.
      </p>
    </statement>
    
    <solution>
      <p>
        asdf
      </p>
    </solution>
  </task>
  
  <task>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Is the pullback of a total order along an injective map necessarily a total order? If so, prove it. If not, provide a counterexample.
      </p>
    </statement>
    
    <solution>
